Pre-Game Insights: England and Australia are set to battle with each other in the 2nd T20I of the ongoing series on September 13, 2024.
The venue of ENG vs AUS 2nd T20I is Sophia Gardens in Cardiff, UK.
Mitchell Marsh leads Australia while Phil Salt leads England.
Both sides have played 25 matches. England have won 11 while Australia have won 12. Two games ended with no result.
In the recent 5 clashes between both sides, the hosts have won 2 games while the visitors Aussies have won 2 matches. 1 encounter witnessed no result.
Aaron Finch has scored the most 619 runs for the Aussies vs England.
Shane Watson has the best bowling figures with his 4/15 vs ENG in 2011.
Jos Buttler is the leading run-scorer vs Australia with 584 runs.
Chris Jordan and Adil Rashid have the most wickets to their names (13).
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Englishmen have been quite powerful at home in England vs Australia encounters. Out of 10 T20I games, England has won 6 and lost only 3.
England also won the only game played at Cardiff against Australia in the past in 2015.
